description.narrative: Communities, parents, caregivers and children have increased awareness of the consequences of violence and have the skills to protect children and women.,which contributes to Access To Justice, Prevention And Response Services For Violence Against Children. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Advocacy And Public Engagement, Developing And Leveraging Resources And Partnerships, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: By 2022, girls, boys and women nationally have increased access to and utilize preventive and responsive protection services that promote their safety, well-being and access to justice.

description.narrative: UNICEF expanded the implementation of Parenting for Child Development programme (P4CD) through DFAT Church Partnership Programme to engage two additional partners, thereby reaching two additional provinces. With this increase, 60 newly trained facilitators reached over 1,980 parents and 7,500 children in 6 provinces. UNICEF advocacy with Government resulted in institutionalization of the P4CD programme in their annual workplan for 2020, thereby ensuring sustainability and ownership. As part of the End Violence Against Children awareness campaign, a 45-episodes radio drama series was finalized and launched in August 2019, in collaboration with the National Broadcasting Commission, reaching approximately 460,000 listeners. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:10/08/2020
